headline: Starbucks slashes its menu, removing 13 drinks
summary: When Starbucks removes menu items, the chain knows it's going to anger some customers. That's why it has traditionally not made mass changes to its permanent menu. headline: Starbucks Cup Recycling Push Adds New Dimension To Investment Story
summary: Starbucks expanded U.S. cup recycling access, focusing on polypropylene cold beverage cups. The company reports that more than 60% of U.S. households can now recycle Starbucks cold cups. This packaging shift forms part of a broader sustainability initiative aimed at supporting a circular economy. For investors watching NasdaqGS:SBUX, this sustainability update comes with the stock at a recent close of $91.95. The shares show a 9.5% return over the past 30 days and year to date, compared...

headline: AI Capex Clouds The Tech Horizon, Even As Meta And Tesla Shine
summary: On Thursday, Nasdaq fell 1.3% as the market digested mixed results from some Mag 7 reports. The primary weight came from Microsoft. AI spending anxiety rippled through the software sector.

headline: Polypropylene Cups Earn Widely Recyclable Designation, Expanding Access to Curbside Recycling Nationwide
summary: NEW YORK, February 02, 2026--More communities across the U.S. can now recycle cold to‑go cups, marking a major step toward reducing waste and building a more circular future. Thanks to the leadership of How2Recycle®, NextGen Consortium managed by Closed Loop Partners’ Center for the Circular Economy, The Recycling Partnership, Starbucks and WM, to‑go cups are entering a new era of recyclability.
